**X[2] <= 0.009**. Given X[2] = 0.01 -> go **right**.  \n","- Next split: **X[3] <= 0.024**. Given X[3] = 0.03 -> go **right**.  \n","So the prediction is the value at the rightmost leaf: **Y_hat = 242.369**.\n","\n","### 3e) Leaf with the lowest difference between actual Y and predictions  \n","In the tree plot, the leaf’s **squared_error** summarizes within-node squared error (residual variation).  \n","The smallest squared_error among leaves is **2121.133** (leftmost leaf), so that leaf has the **lowest typical difference** between actual Y and predicted Y.\n","\n","### 3f) Observed min_samples_split value  \n","The smallest internal node that still split has **137** samples (the node splitting on X[3]).  \n","So, based on what is observable in the tree, the effective min_samples_split must allow a split at **137** samples (i.e., it is <= 137).  \n","The smallest split we can observe occurred at **137** samples.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"a83f4745","metadata":{"id":"a83f4745"},"source":["## Question 4 (15 points)\n","**Orange dataset**: predict **age** from **circumference**.\n","\n","Must test at least three regression equations using techniques covered in class, then select one final equation and justify.\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":24,"id":"f42da025","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"f42da025","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1771883281657,"user_tz":300,"elapsed":33,"user":{"displayName":"Jessica Vargas","userId":"04622878135586132667"}},"outputId":"c104abe4-954d-4964-c43a-3d9ccd033645"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["(    age  circumference\n"," 0   118             30\n"," 1   484             58\n"," 2   664             87\n"," 3  1004            115\n"," 4  1231            120,\n"," (35, 2))"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":24}],"source":["# Load Orange dataset\n","orange_df = pd.read_csv('/content/Orange.csv')\n","orange_df.head(), orange_df.shape\n"]},{"cel